amp; Decrypt Script\n\nA helper script is installed at `~/.local/bin/gh-issue-decrypt`. Usage:\n\n```bash\n# Scan all open issues in a repo for encrypted content\ngh-issue-decrypt OWNER/REPO\n\n# Decrypt a specific issue\ngh-issue-decrypt OWNER/REPO 42\n```\n\n## Issue Format Convention\n\nSenders can mix plaintext and encrypted blocks in the same issue:\n\n```markdown\n## Bug Report\n\nThis part is public context about the issue.\n\n[enc:age]\n-----BEGIN AGE ENCRYPTED FILE-----\n...\n-----END AGE ENCRYPTED FILE-----\n[/enc:age]\n\nMore public context here if needed.\n```\n\nThe `[enc:age]` / `[/enc:age]` markers are optional but help agents\ndistinguish encrypted blocks from other base64 content. The script also\ndetects bare `BEGIN AGE ENCRYPTED FILE` headers without markers.\n\n## Authentication Caveat\n\nage encrypts but does **not** authenticate the sender. Anyone with your\npublic key can encrypt to you. If you need to verify who sent a message,\nhave senders also sign their plaintext with:\n\n- **SSH signatures** (`ssh-keygen -Y sign`) — easiest if they already have SSH keys\n- **minisign** (`minisign -S`) — lightweight Ed25519 signing tool\n\n## Security Notes\n\n- Private key has `chmod 600` — only your user can read it\n- The private key never leaves your machine\n- X25519 (Curve25519 Diffie-Hellman) — 128-bit security level\n- age armor is safe to paste in Markdown; no special escaping needed\n- Back up `~/.config/age/issuebot.key` — if lost, encrypted messages are unrecoverable\n\n## Installation Summary\n\nEverything is already set up on this machine:\n\n```\nage 1.2.1              → /usr/bin/age\nPrivate key            → ~/.config/age/issuebot.key (600)\nScanner script         → ~/.local/bin/gh-issue-decrypt\n```\n&quot;
